 06.004. Effective 05/09/2017. 06.004 Faculty Reappointment, Tenure, and Promotion New Policy The original Reappointment, Tenure, and Promotion policy was broken into several smaller policies. 06.004 is one of the break out policies. March 07, 2017 06.003 Student Academic Integrity Revision Revised to bring the policy in compliance with the 6 year review cycle, and to align with the policy content with the current policy template standards. The revisions include clarification of instructor and AIO responsibilities; addition of section on students, who do not have a current relationship with the university, being subjects to the disciplinary process for conduct that occurred while they had relationship with the university; addition of degree revocation; and clarification of the duration of each stage of the disciplinary process. Effective 03/07/2017. 06.046 Centers and Institutes Revision Revised to align with new procedure for reviewing Centers and Institutes and assessment tracking per SACS recommendations. Effective 03/07/2017. January 19, 2017 04.016 Use of Alcoholic Beverages Revision Revised to allow the sale of alcohol in the Syndicate (in the University Union) and Faculty/Staff Club. Additionally, revised to allow sales of alcohol in the Faculty/Staff Club at 4:00 pm. Effective 01/19/2017. January 12, 2017 10.024 Sales and Receipt of Funds Revision Revised to ensure proper handling of the university's assets, improve compliance, and address the needs of the current cash handling environment. Effective 01/12/2017. 10.035 Accepting Credit Cards Revision Revised to ensure proper handling of the university's assets, improve compliance, and address the needs of the current cash handling environment. Effective 01/12/2017. Pages1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 … next › last » RSS Feed Top Main Menu Home FAQ Policy manual Resources Policy updates About the Policy Office University Links MyUNT Blackboard EagleConnect UNT Directory UNT Map UNT Calendar Jobs at UNT Give to UNT Email &